# Coordinative Actualization: How the Definite Emerges, Coheres, and Runs Forward

*Third paper in the Concordius series. Companion to "Modeling Reality as a [[Appendix I - Dictionary of Terms#Gelfand Triple|Gelfand Triple]]" and "From the Cogito to the [[Appendix I - Dictionary of Terms#Logos|Logos]]." This is the scientist's door: it reads the created world as the physicist meets it, in structural and mathematical terms. The names the older traditions give to what is described here — and the theology that follows from them — are taken up at the head of the next paper, where the three readings are gathered before the crossing.*

---

## Abstract

Look at the created world. Out of a sea of possibility, definite outcomes condense — continuously, everywhere, one actual result drawn from a distribution of what might have been — and they do not scatter into noise; they cohere, into a single world consistent with itself, running in one direction in time. This is among the things the scientist studies and has never fully closed: how the indefinite becomes definite (the measurement problem, the quantum-to-classical transition), why the separate outcomes agree into one consistent history, and why the whole runs forward (the arrow of time). This paper gives that process a structure. A single actualization event is a spectral collapse — one eigenstate drawn from the distributional potential of Φ′, the GNST of Paper 1 made operative in time. Creation taken whole is the coordination of every such event into one coherent manifold; the structure that does the coordinating is the nuclear topology τ_nuclear; and time and space are not the stage on which this happens but its products.

One point about freedom belongs here because it is so often misplaced. The mechanism of actualization is fixed — the spectral theorem is the one form in which an eternal structure can yield temporal outcomes, and it is not chosen. What is contingent is the actualized *content*: which eigenstate is drawn, at each event, from among those the structure makes coherent. Whatever freedom or contingency the world exhibits lives not in the type of the mechanism but in what is selected within it, continuously, at every moment of creation.

**Confidence tier notice:** All sections of this paper derive from the framework established in the first two papers and carry the same mathematical warrant. The paper makes no appeal to testimony; it stays within what the Gelfand triple and the spectral theorem supply.

