## 1. Introduction

Begin where the scientist begins: with the world, not with a name for it. The world we observe is definite. Whatever lies beneath it — and a century of physics has found that beneath it behaves as a genuine distribution of possibilities, not a veil over already-definite facts — what we encounter is one outcome at a time: this result, this position, this history, drawn from a spread of what could have occurred. And the outcomes are not independent. They agree. The world that condenses out of possibility is consistent with itself — one classical reality, shared, on which every measurement can be made to fit — and it runs in a single direction, past to future, against which no process is observed to move. The emergence of the definite from the indefinite, the agreement of the definite into one history, and the directionality of the whole are three faces of a single fact about creation that the natural sciences describe with great precision and explain only in part.

This paper is the structural account of that fact, and the two papers before it built what it stands on. Paper 1 showed that reality admits a rigorous model as a rigged Hilbert space and named the engine by which an eternal structure yields temporal outcomes: the GNST, the continuous actualization. Paper 2 added the one datum no observer can deny — that there is someone here observing — and used it to characterize the structures. Neither paper supplied the world. The Gelfand triple is atemporal; it holds the complete space of possibilities and the selection of none of them. The world is the selecting, going on — and the world's *coherence,* that the selections cohere into one order rather than a heap, is what this paper is about.

The event by which the indefinite becomes definite is a spectral collapse: the GNST drawing one eigenstate from the distributional potential of Φ′. That much is established in Paper 1 and is not re-derived here. What this paper follows is the *result* — that the manifold of collapse-events is coordinated, held into a single coherent, convergent creation, by the nuclear topology τ_nuclear. Read from the result side, creation is coordinative actualization: definite outcomes drawn one at a time, and integrated, as they are drawn, into one consistent and continuous world.

