## 4. What This Paper Established, and What Comes Next

A single collapse yields one outcome. Creation entire is the whole manifold of outcomes, held coherent: definite results drawn continuously from the distributional potential of Φ′, coordinated by the nuclear topology τ_nuclear into one consistent, convergent, forward-running world, with time and space constituted by the sequence of events rather than presupposed by it. The measurement problem, the preferred-basis problem, the consistency of the classical record, and the arrow of time are, read structurally, four faces of one coordination. The mechanism is fixed and not chosen; what is contingent is which eigenstate is actualized at each event.

This is as far as the science carries on its own. Two questions remain open at the end of it, and the next paper takes them up. First: what is the structure of the descent — why does the created order densify into the particular layered hierarchy of constraint levels it has, and what crossings does that descent require? Second: the coordinating activity described here, and the freedom in the selection, have long been described from the inside under other names; the older readings — the mathematician's, the believer's, and now the scientist's — converge on this same structure, and the threshold paper gathers all three before the crossing into the matter that follows.

